                                    <p>We have three users:</p>
                                    <p>Faculty: The post "jobs/tasks" including, dates/times, number of hours, place, description. The tasks can be
                                        recurrent and it can include a number of individuals (considered the option of signing up and fill slots). A
                                        faculty can assign the task to a class (consider the need of integrating with HR/classes system) and of course
                                        to a quarter. But only to classes what the instructor is teaching. IDEAL: This can be integrated potentially
                                        with Canvas as an assignment. The CANVAS API could do this although this is out of scope for this quarter</p>

                                    <p>Staff: Staff can post tasks (similar to the one Sapan posted today). They are not necessarily related to a class
                                        but a faculty can "copy the task" and assign it to a class and give extra credit</p>

                                    <p>NOTE: Consider providing a way to open tasks only for students or the community in general.
                                    </p>

                                    <p>Students can sign up to the tasks, make comments, send messages to the staff/faculty. Students should be able
                                        to withdraw themselves from a task. In general, an admin process should allow faculty/staff to delete/update/add
                                        tasks.
                                    </p>

                                    <p>For all the account on the system (faculty, staff, students), eventually, we may be able to integrate with Canvas
                                        and get the minimum information (profile picture, name and ID).</p>

                                    <p>The system should provide a way to get notifications by SMS, or email.</p>

